    "headline": "Insurer Private-Credit Exposure Jumped 21% Last Year",
    "summary": "Private-credit investments held by U.S. life insurance companies jumped 21% –or $83 billion– in 2025, more than double the 9% growth of overall assets, according to research by Barclays.  Insurers aren’t at risk of the massive investor withdrawals hitting private-credit funds, but they may not be reserving enough capital to cover potential losses from the investments, Barclays said.  The private credit ratings assigned to the deals might be too high, resulting in insufficient balance-sheet offsets.",
